Because `if` is an expression, we can use it on the right side of a `let` declaration to dynamically assign a variable!

```rust
let condition = true;
let number = if condition { 5 } else { 6 };
```

Notice there are **no semicolons** inside the blocks. That means the block evaluates to the number `5` or `6`!

When doing a `let if`, the types returned by each block **must** strictly be the same.

```rust
let condition = true;
// ERROR! Expected integer, found String
let number = if condition { 5 } else { "six" };
```

Variables must have a single defined type at compile time!
